%% Book reference: Chapter 10, §10.2
%% Render at: https://mermaid.live

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> CLOSED : initial state

    CLOSED --> CLOSED : ✓ call succeeds\nfailure_count = 0

    CLOSED --> CLOSED : ✗ call fails\nfailure_count < threshold

    CLOSED --> OPEN : ✗ call fails\nfailure_count >= threshold\n(failure_threshold = 3)

    OPEN --> OPEN : any call → CircuitOpenError\n(fast-fail, no tool execution)

    OPEN --> HALF_OPEN : recovery_timeout elapsed\n(default: 30 seconds)

    HALF_OPEN --> CLOSED : ✓ trial call succeeds\nfailure_count = 0

    HALF_OPEN --> OPEN : ✗ trial call fails\nback to OPEN

    note right of OPEN
        During OPEN state:
        all calls return
        Err(CircuitOpenError)
        immediately — the tool's
        execute() is never called.
        This prevents cascading
        failure propagation.
    end note

    note right of HALF_OPEN
        Only half_open_max_calls
        (default: 1) trial call
        is permitted. All others
        are rejected like OPEN.
    end note
